caption: I’ve been from eating here for at least the last 15 years and it pains me to say this but I’ll never order from here again. Aside from the fact that a sandwich now costs $12.50 (up from the $8.50 a few years ago) the quality of product has gone down. The reason I’m done eating here is that I ordered a sandwich on Monday March 29 and have been suffering from food poisoning since. The sandwich was extremely greasy and the meat was a little tough but hey it’s a cheesesteak so I chalked it up. I hate to point fingers but this was the only thing I ate differently from my family that day so if there’s only one conclusion I can draw, I got sick from that sandwich. I hate to knock a Brooklyn staple but I needed to be honest.

Ordered delivery yesterday because the water in my building was turned off (without notice!) and so cooking was not happening. I read some reviews first and was pretty convinced based off those alone (except for that guy who ate like 1/3 of his cheesesteak and then took a picture of what was left and said he overpaid for too small of a cheesesteak. What planet is he on?).  Placing the order was a breeze, and the person on the other end of the phone couldn't have been nicer! The delivery arrived in less time than anticipated. Finally, food was great! Husband and I were both happy with the Philly cheesesteak (with the works) and the onion rings. The price was very reasonable as well.  Great experience and adding this place to our list of takeout restaurant rotations. Thanks guys!
